text: Google Search is a web search engine originally developed in 1997 and the flagship service operated by Google.
Bing is a web search engine operated by Microsoft. Launched in 2009. The service evolved from Microsoft's previous search engines: MSN Search, Windows Live Search and later Live Search.
Daum Search is a search engine operated by Kakao, a South Korean internet company established in 2014 following the merger of Daum Communications and Kakao
Yandex Search is a web search engine and the flagship service of  the Russian corporation Yandex.
Baidu Search is a search engine and flagship service operated by the Chinese web services company Baidu, Inc., which was incorporated in 2000.
